{"search_data": "HaryanaHaryana Affordable Housing Policy (PMAY) 2018 for Area Outside Core Limits Haryana cabinet approves Affordable Housing Policy 2018 for area falling within municipal limits (outside core limits) under Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) to provide more houses to identified PMAY beneficiariesHaryana Affordable Housing Policy (PMAY) 2018Haryana cabinet committee meeting held on 15 November 2018 approves Affordable Housing Policy (PMAY) 2018 under the chairmanship of CM Manohar Lal Khattar. This new policy is for areas outside the core limits which lie within the municipal limits.Affordable Housing Policy (AHP) is going to encourage the planning and completion of Group Housing Projects. In these projects, apartments of pre-defined size are made available at pre defined rates within a target time frame to ensure increased supply of affordable housing in the residential sectors falling in municipal limits.These apartments are predominantly given to the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojna (PMAY) beneficiaries as identified by the department of Urban Local Bodies (ULBs). All these projects are required to be essentially completed within 2 years from the approval of building plans or grant of environmental clearance (whichever is later).Maximum allotment rate is Rs. 3500 per sq.ft in Gurugram and Faridabad, Rs. 3000 per sq.ft in Panchkula and Pinjore and Kalka, Rs. 2500 per sq.ft in Karnal, Ambala, Hisar, Yamunanagar, Rohtak, Kurukshetra, Bahadurgarh, Bawal, Rewari, Palwal, Hodal, Dharuhera and Ganaur and Rs. 2100 per sq.ft in rest of the development plans.This will help in achieving the motive of Housing for all and to maximize the benefit to the intended beneficiaries identified in the PMAY.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}